we don't support usage: 

```
// Custom "step.answers[i].xxx" fields registration
  useEffect(() => {
    // fired once when the key is changed in <Answers key="">
    fields.forEach((answer, index) =>
      ANSWER_KEYS.forEach((answerKey) => {
        register({
          name: `step.answers[${index}].${answerKey}`,
          value: fields[index][answerKey]
        });
      })
    );

    return () => {
      fields.forEach((answer, index) =>
        ANSWER_KEYS.forEach((answerKey) => {
          unregister(`step.answers[${index}].${answerKey}`);
        })
      );
    };
  }, [fields, ANSWER_KEYS]);
  ```
  
you can try with `shouldUnregister: false`, this wouldn't work for the next major version as well. field inputs need to be in the render for us to manipulate the field array.

Okay. Is the following code supported?

```js
// <FieldsComponent />
const { fields } = useFieldsArray({ name: 'step.fields', control });
...
return {fields.map((field, index) =>
        Object.keys(field).map((fieldKey) => (
          <input
            ref={register()}
            key={`${index}-${fieldKey}`}
            style={{ display: 'none' }}
            value={field[fieldKey]}
            name={`step.answers[${index}].${fieldKey}`}
          />
        ))
      )}
