My Gosh! Spent a few days and found the reason for the error above. 

The data that I pass as default values is immutable. It's frozen with [deepFreeze](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/freeze)

**The next code throws an error**
```js
function deepFreeze(object) {
  // Retrieve the property names defined on object
  const propNames = Object.getOwnPropertyNames(object);

  // Freeze properties before freezing self

  for (const name of propNames) {
    const value = object[name];

    if (value && typeof value === "object") {
      deepFreeze(value);
    }
  }

  return Object.freeze(object);
}

deepFreeze([{a: 1}]).pop()
```
that's why `defaultValues.pop()` in the library leads to the `Cannot delete property '0' of [object Array]`

The solution can be `[...defaultValues].pop()` or a deep copy of values `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(defaultValues))`.
Not sure what is better for performance, especially for the IE version.

